        "origin": "web-extension",
        "content": "<p> The Dead Sea Scrolls and the Rabbinic Mishna also refer to Samuel as “the Seer.” He is called a Nazirite (<em>Nazîrî</em>; related to the Arabic word <em>nadhr </em>[vow] from the root <em>NDhR</em>). We will speak further about the vows of the Nazirite when we discuss the Virgin Mary below.  </p>",
